nodes.text: A cure? What, are you crazy? Do I look like I want to be cured? You want to make me feel better, sugar? Give me some more Jet.
Hey there. You want to spend some time with Fannie?
I don't want to do this anymore. Me an my fella' are going to get away from here and live life straight. Just as soon as I can pay off Lou.
Hey there, you came back. Looking for a little fun, or did you come back to give me some money  for Lou?
Uh, I know, and I'm real grateful...but I guess I owed Lou more than I thought. I need more  money.
Well, yes...but it turns out that I owe Lou more than I thought.
Thanks again. I can't wait to tell my guy. We'll be out of here as soon as his leg  heals up.

(Fannie looks distinctly unhealthy as she wobbles towards you) Hey there, lover. I'm feeling a little under the weather lately. Want to give me some money for a quick boost? I can make it worth your while. (grins) (Fannie doesn't look very well at all) Hey there, lady, spare some money? Or a bit o' Jet fuel even?
You've been so nice to me. I felt that you really meant something when you did that. (sob) I sure wish it was like that all the time.
Nice and slow, baby. I'll show you a real nice time for your $60.
Yeah, that's what I need. Oh yeah. What a rush. Mmmmm...
Oh, you're just full of great ideas now, aren't you. Well, I don't need you. Plenty of people still want to pay for Fannie's charms. If you won't give me money for Jet, then just get out of my sight.
Hello, sister. Looking for work?

(Fannie looks distinctly unhealthy as she wobbles towards you) Hey there, lover. I'm feeling a little under the weather lately. Want to give me some money for a quick boost? I can make it worth your while. (grins) (Fannie doesn't look very well at all) Hey there, pal. Ready for a li'l fun with Fannie? Half-price for you, lover. Where'd I put my Jet?
Always nice to get some repeat business. For you, I'll even change the sheets.

Yeah, well...I owe Lou some money and I can't leave until I pay her off. But as soon as I do (sniff) I'm going to take my beau and get myself as far away from this life as I can. If I could only raise a little extra dough.
All I need now is $200 and I'm in the clear. My man and I are out of here clean and free. No more strange, grubby, people pawing at me all day and night. Uh, I didn't mean no offense.
Maybe you'll last a bit longer this time, honey. You'll get more of your $60 worth that way.
That's okay, baby. You've already helped enough. (sniff) I only need another $150, though.
Oh thank you,thank you. I didn't think that there was anyone this kind outside of my dreams. You're the best. Thanks again. Hey, want a freebie? On the house?

(Fannie looks distinctly unhealthy as she wobbles towards you) Hey there, lover. I'm feeling a little under the weather lately. Want to give me some money for a quick boost? I can make it worth your while. (grins) (Fannie looks distinctly unhealthy as she wobbles towards you) Hey there, sister. Can you spare a few bucks to help a gal who's down on her luck? Just 'til I get back on my feet again.

He really wants to, but he's just barely getting by as a miner. We keep hoping he'll make a big strike but that hasn't happened yet. And last week a beam fell on him and broke his leg, so he can't work. Now I have to give him what little money I can spare 'til he gets better.
You know, back-floppin' work. Even the way you look, you could make some money. Those miners ain't too particular, ya know.
Well it shore helps if'n your nose ain't to keen. Those miners ain't too fond of soap and water.

links.text: Well, I guess just a little more to get you by wouldn't hurt. Here's some Jet.
You've already had more than enough Jet. Last thing I need to do is watch another Jet reliant.  Goodbye.
Sure, sounds good to me. Good thing I caught you before you left.
Sure, sounds good to me. Good thing I caught you before you left.
Didn't I give you some money so you could stop doing this?
Pay off Lou?
Hey, I gave you money already. What are you talking about?
Just stopping by, Fannie. Goodbye.
Just here for some fun this time, Fannie. We'll see how it goes.
How much do you need for Lou?
Just here for some fun this time, Fannie. We'll see how it goes.
Well, you've got all you're going to from me. Good bye.
I can't believe it! How much more money do you need to get out of this?
I've heard enough of this. Goodbye.
How much more?
That was quite a thank you, Fannie. I just better get myself out of here while I can still walk.  You're welcome. Goodbye.
Well, when you're with me, it is.
Thanks for the offer, but maybe another time would be better. Goodbye.
$60, huh? Sounds like a good price to me. Here's my money.
Uh, well, I guess I'll just let you enjoy yourself now. Goodbye.
I have something that should cure you of that reliance on Jet.
Find yourself another sucker, Fannie. Goodbye.
Uh, I was just looking around. Goodbye.
You sure know how to make a guy feel special. Thanks.
Uh, I think I've changed my mind. See you around, Fannie. Goodbye.
You sure know how to make a guy feel special. Thanks.
That's a sad story, but you should have the money you need soon enough. As long as you keep your back to the mattress, that is. Goodbye.
How much extra money do you need to pay off Lou?
Can't your boyfriend help you out of debt?
None taken. I don't really paw, do I? Anyhow, I could pay your way out of here. Here's $200.
Sounds sad, alright. Well, I guess you'd better get busy then. Goodbye.
Thanks for the offer, but maybe another time would be better. Goodbye.
$60, huh? Sounds like a good price to me. Here's my money.
Well, I guess if that's all you need. But this is it. I mean it.
Yeah, sure. I'm out of here. Goodbye.
That's not really necessary, Fannie. Just use the money to get yourself out of this life. Goodbye.
Why sure, Fannie. I think I'll take you up on that offer.
Sounds as though you two have had some bad luck. How much did you say you need?
I don't think that's for me. Goodbye.
You think so? Hmm, maybe I should.
Really? Maybe this isn't for me after all. Thanks for the offer, though. Goodbye.
